<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,266,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,303,266,292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: male (macropterous, N= 
<number box="[759,774,266,292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
) 
<quantity box="[790,963,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.485" metricValueMax="2.52" metricValueMin="2.45" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.485" valueMax="2.52" valueMin="2.45">2.45–2.52 mm</quantity>
, (brachypterous, N= 
<number box="[1209,1219,266,292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
) 
<quantity box="[1236,1344,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.49" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.49">2.49 mm</quantity>
; female (macropterous, N= 
<number box="[374,389,306,332]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
) 
<quantity box="[404,577,306,332]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9749999999999996" metricValueMax="3.05" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.9749999999999996" valueMax="3.05" valueMin="2.9">2.90–3.05 mm</quantity>
, (brachypterous, N= 
<number box="[822,832,306,332]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
) 
<quantity box="[848,956,306,332]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.72" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="2.72">2.72 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,266,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,285,346,372]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Colour</emphasis>
. General color brown. Vertex and antennae yellowish brown, submedian carinae of vertex bordered by blackish brown laterally. Frons and clypeus yellowish brown to tawny brown, in some specimens frons sordid white medially. Pronotum blackish brown laterally. Tegmina hyaline and lustrous, macropterous forewings speckled with dark brown flecks, apex of clavus with dark spot (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1096,466,492]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1078,1096,466,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); in brachypterous form with apical margin and apex of clavus black (
<figureCitation box="[625,697,506,532]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[680,697,506,532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Dorsum and venter of abdomen with irregular sordid patches laterally on each segment. Legs yellowish brown to tawny brown except fore- and midcoxae black. Male pygofer with parameres and anal segment blackish brown. Ovipositor brown to sordid yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,266,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,266,626,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Head</emphasis>
. Including eyes narrower than pronotum (
<number box="[763,895,626,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.755" valueMax="0.77" valueMin="0.74">0.74–0.77</number>
: 
<number box="[899,909,626,652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
). Vertex elongate, longer medially than wide at base about 
<number box="[311,352,666,692]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.4">1.4</number>
: 
<number box="[363,378,666,692]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
, anterior margin rounded, submedian carinae uniting before apex of vertex, lateral carinae sinuate, slightly converging anteriorly, posterior margin nearly straight or concave medially (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1306,706,732]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1293,1306,706,732]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view meeting lateral carinae of frons with approximately right angle at fastigium, submedian carinae slightly raised above level of lateral carinae until just beyond fastigium (
<figureCitation box="[921,994,786,812]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[978,994,786,812]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frons in midline longer than maximum width about 
<number box="[366,412,826,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="2.6">2.6</number>
: 
<number box="[417,428,826,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
, widest at level of ocelli, lateral carinae subparallel below ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1273,826,852]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1256,1273,826,852]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Postclypeus and anteclypeus with distinct median carinae, together approximately 
<number box="[990,1042,866,892]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.75">0.75</number>
x length of frons, in profile shallowly convex (
<figureCitation box="[328,400,906,932]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[384,400,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Postclypeus slightly wider than frons at apex (
<figureCitation box="[976,1049,906,932]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1032,1049,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antennae cylindrical, reaching frontoclypeal suture, segment I about as long as wide, shorter than segment II about 
<number box="[1147,1163,946,972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
: 2.0 (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1302,946,972]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1285,1302,946,972]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,266,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,292,986,1012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum in dorsal view approximately 
<number box="[775,827,986,1012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.63">0.63</number>
x length of vertex, posterior margin deeply cleft, lateral carinae reaching posterior margin, converging apically (
<figureCitation box="[907,981,1026,1052]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[968,981,1026,1052]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), pronotum width 
<number box="[1224,1344,1026,1052]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.7749999999999999" valueMax="0.83" valueMin="0.72">0.72–0.83</number>
, length 
<number box="[151,272,1066,1092]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.2" valueMax="0.22" valueMin="0.18">0.18–0.22</number>
. Mesonotum in macropterous form 
<quantity box="[697,868,1066,1092]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.56" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.54">0.54–0.58 mm</quantity>
long, in brachypterous form 
<quantity box="[1215,1321,1066,1092]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5999999999999996" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.36">0.36 mm</quantity>
long, lateral carinae extending to posterior margin, median carina obscure apically (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1110,1106,1132]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1096,1110,1106,1132]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tegmina in macropterous form 
<quantity box="[218,362,1146,1172]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.8">2.8–3.2 mm</quantity>
long, surpassing tip of abdomen by nearly one third of its total length, in brachypterous form attaining or surpassing end of 
<number box="[576,590,1186,1212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
th abdominal segment, widest at middle portion, rounded apically (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,168,1226,1252]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs with tibia normal (not expanded), metatibia 
<quantity box="[766,936,1226,1252]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="8.4" metricValueMin="7.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="0.8" valueMax="0.84" valueMin="0.76">0.76–0.84 mm</quantity>
long, metabasitarsus (
<number box="[1196,1317,1226,1252]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.39" valueMax="0.42" valueMin="0.36">0.36–0.42</number>
) nearly as long as tarsomere 
<number box="[366,381,1266,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<number box="[397,518,1266,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.16" valueMax="0.18" valueMin="0.14">0.14–0.18</number>
) + 
<number box="[558,573,1266,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number box="[589,710,1266,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.27" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.24">0.24–0.30</number>
) combined, calcar (
<number box="[942,1063,1266,1292]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="0.335" valueMax="0.34" valueMin="0.33">0.33–0.34</number>
) slightly shorter than metabasitarsus, thick foliaceous, tectiform, with 
<number box="[616,689,1306,1332]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="16.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="15.0">15–17</number>
small, black-tipped marginal teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,266,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1346,1372]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Abdomen</emphasis>
(except genitalia). Male drumming organ with 
<number box="[908,923,1346,1372]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
elongate apodemes directed dorsocaudad, nearly attaining tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,266,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,1426,1452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view with laterodorsal angle angulately produced caudad, wider ventrally than dorsally, laterocaudal margins sinuate (
<figureCitation box="[750,824,1466,1492]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[807,824,1466,1492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Diaphragm narrow, mediodorsal process strongly sclerotised and concave medially, directed dorsocaudad, ornamented with numerous tiny teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1420,1506,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1404,1420,1506,1532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Parameres broad, long, tips converging laterally basad, tip expanded (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1111,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[1079,1111,1546,1572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus laterally compressed, curved dorsad, gradually narrowing towards pointed apex, submedially with 
<number box="[1192,1207,1586,1612]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="4.0">4</number>
distally acuminate spine-like processes, 
<number box="[401,416,1626,1652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
on the left side and 
<number box="[653,667,1626,1652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
to the right on dorsal side, gonopore subapical on ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[159,332,1666,1692]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Figs 9, 11, 
<number box="[299,332,1666,1692]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Suspensorium rectangular, strap-like (
<figureCitation box="[809,898,1666,1692]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[866,898,1666,1692]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
), fused with the dorsal base of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[159,327,1706,1732]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Figs 9, 11, 
<number box="[295,327,1706,1732]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Opening for parameres large, dorsal margin arched upward, medially nearly straight, lateral margins slightly sinuate, ventral margin concave (
<figureCitation box="[735,806,1746,1772]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[790,806,1746,1772]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
