<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName box="[788,882,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis box="[788,882,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">L. picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the characters used in the key. Furthermore, the distributions are distinct (
<taxonomicName box="[494,615,189,214]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcuata">
<emphasis box="[494,615,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">L. arcuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in central southern 
<collectingCountry box="[848,918,189,215]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">China</collectingCountry>
while 
<taxonomicName box="[998,1093,189,214]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis box="[998,1093,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">L. picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1265,1340,189,215]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="66">China</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
